@startuml
title Threading Model Overview

skinparam ParticipantPadding 8

actor "External caller" as Caller
participant "Application owner/platform thread" as PlatformThread
participant "WindowRegistry" as Registry
participant "PlatformRuntime / IFrame" as Platform
participant "Window event queues" as EventQueues
participant "Update jthread" as UpdateThread
participant "Render jthread" as RenderThread
participant "WindowHost" as Host
participant "RenderModule snapshot mutex" as SnapshotMutex

Caller -> PlatformThread : createWindow(), run(), quit()
PlatformThread -> Registry : create/store Window
PlatformThread -> Platform : pollEvents()
Platform -> EventQueues : enqueue Frame/Mouse/Keyboard records

par update thread
	UpdateThread -> Registry : windows()
	UpdateThread -> EventQueues : drain family queues
	UpdateThread -> UpdateThread : update input state and widget tree
	UpdateThread -> SnapshotMutex : publish new RenderSnapshot
else render thread
	RenderThread -> Registry : windows()
	RenderThread -> Host : makeCurrent()
	Host -> Host : bind/validate render thread id
	RenderThread -> SnapshotMutex : read current RenderSnapshot
	RenderThread -> RenderThread : execute commands and present
else platform thread
	PlatformThread -> EventQueues : drain PlatformAction queue
	PlatformThread -> Host : resize/title/requestClosure/validateClosure/releaseFrame
end

note right of EventQueues
Cross-thread handoff is explicit:
platform callbacks enqueue records,
WindowHandle mutators enqueue actions,
and snapshots are swapped under RenderModule's mutex.
end note

note over Host
WindowHost separates platform-thread frame access
from render-thread context access. SurfaceState
invalidation lets the render thread stop safely.
end note

@enduml
